Job Description:
Responsibilities
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. We have several global offices including Los Angeles, New York, Austin, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul, and Tokyo.​

At TikTok, our people are humble, intelligent, compassionate and creative. We create to inspire - for you, for us, and for more than 1 billion users on our platform. We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at TikTok.

About the team
TikTok's content understanding team is seeking experienced Data Scientists, at the Sr. level, to support the company's cutting-edge endeavors in building generative AI. This team is responsible for both supporting AI researchers with annotated data and developing its own LLM/ML tools for optimizing the labeling and model evaluation processes. We seek highly driven, highly motivated individuals desire to work hands-on with this cutting-edge technology.

Responsibilities
This role requires an experienced well-rounded Data Scientist who is able and willing to deeply understand problem domains and iterate quickly in the search for models that both solve stakeholder needs and fulfill technological best practices. Among the responsibilities:

Develop NLP models that accelerate the development of large foundational models and, with the help of a broader team, shepherd them into production;
Mentoring researchers and business stakeholders on best practices for data collection and fine tuning processes for LLMs and other Large Foundational Models;
Collaboratively build a well-considered experiment plan and document results carefully; patiently answer questions from technical and non-technical stakeholders;
Proactive requirements gathering from international stakeholders with diverse professional specialization;
Understand product requirements, drive clarity, and break down technical tasks into smaller units;
To work in a collaborative team of interdependent colleagues; to share code liberally; to scope and accomplish work according to a sprint cycle;
Support researchers and labeling staff to perform investigations when data-related problems arise;
Perform basic project management when delivering an ML solution for large, complex product teams;
Qualifications

We seek candidates with most or all of the following:

Rich, hands-on experience building ML solutions to solve real world business problems;
Intermediate-to-advanced experience with one or more subdomains of NLP, such as natural language understanding (NLU), document processing, information extraction, information retrieval, and dependency parsing; experience with multilingual NLP is "a plus"; hands-on experience fine-tuning encoder-only (e.g., BERT) or decoder-only (e.g., LLaMA) LLM also "a plus";
Knowledge of ML fundamentals, including common algorithms in major paradigms (i.e., supervised, unsupervised, reinforcement), evaluation strategies, optimization (e.g., gradient descent, parameter tuning), and sampling;
Ability to research state-of-the-art algorithms and industry best practices, then apply them to problems at hand;
Excellent written and spoken communication skills for the purpose of communicating with business stakeholders and international teams;
Advanced skills in Python;
Advanced skills in SQL, databases, and general data modeling;
Experience deploying ML models "at scale" and ability to reason about trade-offs (hardware, volume, velocity, model size, etc.);
Knowledge of and experience with "full stack" development, including writing backend API, modifying frontend clients, troubleshooting bottlenecks, and model hosting;
Experience with active learning and human-in-the-loop ML "a plus";
Experience with experiment design "a plus";
Ability and willingness to partake in product design is "a plus";
Project management experience is "a plus"
